caption.text: I didn’t want to say this before as I didn’t want it to come across as a marketing tactic. But we’ve already sold 10/60 since I edited this video - 41 minutes since launching - so: 1% of revenue from this Bootcamp is going to be donated to charitable causes I care about. I haven’t yet settled on a charity, but probably homelessness and education as these things are close to my heart. Day 15: trying to make $300,000 in just 30 days

caption.text:
We’ve all been there - blaming the algorithm for our failures. And the resin it’s so easy to fall into this trap is because there is a reality here! These platforms DO change. And when they do, they can often turn winning content formats into absolute flops. But wallowing doesn’t make things better. In fact it makes it much, much worse. 

And that’s why the best creators I know focus on what they can do to get better - because they understand it’s all they can control. How do they do this? Mindset. The most underrated part of content creation. If you want to develop an iron mindset (as it relates to content) and you have a burning desire to win at social media, comment BOOTCAMP and I’ll add you to the waitlist 🙏

caption.text:
Day 12 of trying to make $300,000 dollars in just 30 days.

Highlights:
- 1700 on waitlist with just 60 spots available 
- Video sales letter ready 
- Landing page almost there
- Emails reviewed
- Fly caught in bare hands
- Living life fully even when it’s terrifying
